phs D.1. and D.2. of Delta National Wildlife Refuge; and by revising paragraph C.1. of Upper Ouachita National Wildlife Refuge to read as follows: §37.37 Louisiana. * * * * * Bayou Sauvage National Wildlife Refuge * * * * * D. Sport Fishing. *␣*␣* 1. Fishing is permitted during daylight hours only. 2. Sport fishing and shellfishing are permitted year round on all refuge lands south of the Intracoastal Waterway; from the banks of U.S. Highway 11; and within the banks of the borrow canal and borrow pits between U.S. Highway 11 and Interstate 10. 3. Only sport fishing with hand-held rod and reel or hand-held rod and line is permitted. Gait shrimp may be taken with cast nets 8 feet in diameter or less. Crawfish and crabs can be taken (up to 100 pounds per person) with wire nets up to 20 inches in diameter. All fishing, crabbing and crawfishing equipment must be attended at all times. 4. The use of trotlines, limblines, slat traps, gar sets, nets or alligator lines is prohibited on the refuge.
